verses.roman:
pūrva-likhita grantha-sūtra-anusāre
yei nāhi likhi, tāhā likhiye vistāre

synonyms: pūrva-likhita—previously mentioned; grantha-sūtra—the synopsis of the pastimes; anusāre—according to; yei—whatever; nāhi likhi—I have not mentioned; tāhā—hat; likhiye—I shall write; vistāre—elaborately.
translation: In accordance with the synopsis previously written, I shall describe in detail whatever I have not mentioned.
